# 🚀 Spring Boot URL Shortener

A simple yet powerful **URL Shortener Service** built with **Spring Boot**, packaged in **Docker**, and deployed on **AWS EC2**.

This project allows users to shorten long URLs into unique **8-character codes** and manage their own links.

---

## ✨ Features

- 🔗 Generate short URLs with **8-character codes**
- 👤 User-based URL management
- 🐳 Packaged with Docker for portability
- ☁️ Deployed on AWS EC2 for scalability
- ⚡ Built with **Spring Boot + Java**

Upcoming features:
- 📊 Analytics (click count, geo-tracking, expiry links)
- 🔒 Authentication

---

## 🛠 Tech Stack

- **Java 17**
- **Spring Boot 3.x**
- **Maven**
- **Docker**
- **AWS EC2 (Ubuntu)**

---

## ⚙️ Project Setup

### 1️⃣ Clone Repository

```bash
git clone https://github.com/your-username/url-shortener.git
cd url-shortener
2️⃣ Build Project with Maven
bash
Copy code
./mvnw clean install
3️⃣ Run Locally
bash
Copy code
./mvnw spring-boot:run
App will be available at:
👉 http://localhost:8080

🐳 Docker Setup
4️⃣ Create Dockerfile
dockerfile
Copy code
# Use OpenJDK as base
FROM openjdk:17-jdk-slim

# Set working directory
WORKDIR /app

# Copy jar file
COPY target/url-shortener-0.0.1-SNAPSHOT.jar app.jar

# Expose port
EXPOSE 8080

# Run the application
ENTRYPOINT ["java", "-jar", "app.jar"]
5️⃣ Build Docker Image
bash
Copy code
docker build -t url-shortener .
6️⃣ Run Docker Container
bash
Copy code
docker run -d -p 8080:8080 --name url-shortener-container url-shortener
Check logs:

bash
Copy code
docker logs -f url-shortener-container
☁️ Deploy on AWS EC2
7️⃣ Launch EC2 Instance
OS: Ubuntu 22.04

Open ports 22 (SSH) and 8080 (App)

8️⃣ Install Docker on EC2
bash
Copy code
sudo apt update
sudo apt install -y docker.io
sudo systemctl start docker
sudo systemctl enable docker
9️⃣ Copy Project Files to EC2
bash
Copy code
scp -i your-key.pem target/url-shortener-0.0.1-SNAPSHOT.jar ubuntu@<EC2_PUBLIC_IP>:/home/ubuntu/
scp -i your-key.pem Dockerfile ubuntu@<EC2_PUBLIC_IP>:/home/ubuntu/
🔟 Build & Run on EC2
bash
Copy code
# SSH into server
ssh -i your-key.pem ubuntu@<EC2_PUBLIC_IP>

# Build docker image
docker build -t url-shortener .

# Run container
docker run -d -p 8080:8080 url-shortener
App will be available at:
👉 http://<EC2_PUBLIC_IP>:8080

📌 API Endpoints
Shorten a URL
http
Copy code
POST /shorten
Content-Type: application/json

{
  "longUrl": "https://example.com/my-very-long-url"
}
Response:

json
Copy code
{
  "shortUrl": "http://localhost:8080/abcd1234"
}
Redirect
http
Copy code
GET /abcd1234
Redirects to original URL.

